						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the wall right of entrance of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Jaitugi, Circa 1200 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The date portion of the inscription is lost. In the introductory portion are mentioned an officer of the king, named Sahadēva and his elder brother <hi rend="italic">Daṇḍēśa</hi> Mallidēva. The stone is broken and all other details are lost.</p>						

						<p>Published in the <hi rend="italic">Epigraphia. Indica,</hi> Vol. V, Page 28 ff.</p>						

						</summary>
